Memcached installed-package testing
===================================

Use this as a smoke test after installing or updating the built packages from a
test repository. The libmemcached command line tools are delivered by the
separate library/libmemcached component and provide useful client-side coverage
for the packaged memcached server.

  pkg list service/memcached library/libmemcached

Save the current SMF service options and the default instance's persistent
enablement flag. The smoke test temporarily changes the service-level
memcached/options property to listen only on localhost; cleanup restores
admin-layer customizations when they existed, or removes the temporary
customizations to expose the previous manifest or profile values. It does not
attempt to preserve transient runtime state such as maintenance, offline, or
dependency-driven states.

  SERVICE_FMRI=svc:/application/database/memcached
  INSTANCE_FMRI=${SERVICE_FMRI}:default
  old_enabled=$(svcprop -p general/enabled "$INSTANCE_FMRI")
  old_enabled_admin=$(svcprop -l all -p general/enabled "$INSTANCE_FMRI" | \
      awk '$3 == "admin" { found = 1 } END { print found ? "true" : "false" }')
  old_options=$(svcprop -p memcached/options "$SERVICE_FMRI")
  old_options_admin=$(svcprop -l all -p memcached/options "$SERVICE_FMRI" | \
      awk '$3 == "admin" { found = 1 } END { print found ? "true" : "false" }')

Configure memcached to listen only on localhost, then start or restart the
default SMF instance.

  pfexec svccfg -s "$SERVICE_FMRI" \
      setprop memcached/options = \( "-l" "127.0.0.1" "-p" "11211" \)
  pfexec svcadm refresh "$SERVICE_FMRI"
  pfexec svcadm enable -rs "$INSTANCE_FMRI"
  pfexec svcadm restart -s "$INSTANCE_FMRI"
  svcs -xv "$INSTANCE_FMRI"

Check basic client connectivity with libmemcached tools.

  memping --servers=127.0.0.1:11211
  printf '%s\n' 'memcached smoke value' > /tmp/memcached-smoke
  memcp --servers=127.0.0.1:11211 /tmp/memcached-smoke
  memcat --servers=127.0.0.1:11211 memcached-smoke
  memstat --servers=127.0.0.1:11211
  memrm --servers=127.0.0.1:11211 memcached-smoke

The memcat output should contain:

  memcached smoke value

Clean up after the smoke test and restore the previous SMF service options
property and persistent instance enablement flag.

  pfexec svcadm disable -s "$INSTANCE_FMRI"
  if [ "$old_options_admin" = true ]; then
      pfexec svccfg -s "$SERVICE_FMRI" \
          setprop memcached/options = \( $old_options \)
  else
      pfexec svccfg -s "$SERVICE_FMRI" delcust -G memcached -P options
  fi
  pfexec svcadm refresh "$SERVICE_FMRI"
  if [ "$old_enabled_admin" = true ]; then
      if [ "$old_enabled" = true ]; then
          pfexec svcadm enable -rs "$INSTANCE_FMRI"
      else
          pfexec svcadm disable -s "$INSTANCE_FMRI"
      fi
  else
      pfexec svccfg -s "$INSTANCE_FMRI" delcust -G general -P enabled
      pfexec svcadm refresh "$INSTANCE_FMRI"
  fi
  rm -f /tmp/memcached-smoke

Related libmemcached verification
=================================

Run the libmemcached component tests as an additional cross-component check
when a memcached update changes protocol behavior, binary protocol handling,
networking, or server startup behavior.

  cd ../libmemcached
  gmake clean test

The libmemcached tests exercise the packaged /usr/lib/memcached binary through
the libmemcached client library and command line tools.
